<h3 id=3D"MicroprocessorandInterfacing-=E2=9C=85Summary.5">=E2=9C=85 <stron=
g>Summary</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Memory Interfacing:</strong> CPU communicates with SRAM and EEPR=
OM using address, data, and control lines.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>I/O Types:</strong> Programmed (polling), interrupt-driven, para=
llel I/O, DMA.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>8255A PPI:</strong> Flexible interface for connecting peripheral=
s.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Devices:</strong> Controlled via CPU output ports, sometimes usi=
ng handshake signals or scanning methods.</p></li>
</ul>
